cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is about learning a distributed representation space for user intent in search, which is a core problem in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also leverages large scale user clicks from Bing search logs as weak supervision, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text classification and clustering. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category. The paper uses machine learning techniques such as end-to-end learning and multi-task learning, which fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses the practical applications of the proposed method in improving search efficiency, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
